name: phosphoenolpyruvate---protein phosphotransferase
classes: Phosphotransferases with a nitrogenous group as acceptor
reaction: phosphoenolpyruvate + protein histidine = pyruvate + protein Npi-phospho-L-histidine [RN:R02628]
comment: Enzyme I of the phosphotransferase system (cf. EC 2.7.1.69 protein-Npi-phosphohistidine---sugar phosphotransferase). Acts only on histidine residues in specific phosphocarrier proteins of low molecular mass (9.5 kDa) involved in bacterial sugar transport. A similar reaction, where the protein is the enzyme EC 2.7.9.2 pyruvate, water dikinase, is part of the mechanism of that enzyme.

references.title: The bacterial phosphoenolpyruvate: sugar phosphotransferase system.
